  "notes": "First closed source-bearing formation Profile under END-CORE, as formalized by ADR-0023, clarified by ADR-0030, and bounded for source stripping by ADR-0036. P0 remains structural experiment evidence. P2 contains decoded natural-language source content, supports formed Endem and reach only, and is not the final release Profile. A future source-stripped release Profile must define retained semantics, source-reference rewriting, loss, disclosure and new identity. Authority-looking identifiers are untrusted selectors rather than authorization proofs, so the standalone file cannot exceed Profile acceptance. ADR-0016 defines abstract maintain time semantics, ADR-0018 defines abstract single-role quantification, ADR-0019 defines abstract measurement and threshold semantics, and ADR-0020 defines abstract all_of/any_of composition semantics, but new Profiles must define their physical fields. Unknown map keys are rejected."
